(1866, 1, '2016-08-13 09:53:27', '2016-08-13 09:53:27', 'Rajkumar Lamichhane is a singer and lyricist by profession. A Kathmandu resident currently living in the Tokyo, Japan, Rajkumar is a very active social philanthropist to help back underprivileged people in Nepal. He’s works as an executive in a company in Tokyo but makes himself available to join the stage shows and the local events to raise money for the kids of Nepal. He frequently travels back to home after gathering resources. He recently provided scholarships to 50 needy students of Baglung district with the resources he raised in Japan. Rajkumar has been leading Sadbhaw’s Japan chapter since 2015.', 'Rajkumar Lamichhane', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'teadas', '', '', '2016-09-03 16:05:56', '2016-09-03 16:05:56', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sadbhaw/?post_type=leader&#038;p=1866', 0, 'leader', '', 0),
(1867, 1, '2016-08-13 09:53:45', '2016-08-13 09:53:45', 'My name is Yangkee Ghale is originally from Kathmandu, Nepal. She is a nursing student currently residing in the Boston, United States. Yangkee strongly believes in being compassionate and helping mankind selflessly in any way possible. So, she wanted to start it with her own native land, Nepal by being a part of an impactful and beautiful cause Sadbhaw Scholarship that aims to help provide education to the needy and deserving Nepali brothers and sisters where education isn''t given the first priority due to poor economic conditions. On behalf of our Nepali brothers and sisters and for the sake of humanity, she requests everyone to help make a positive difference by helping the team of Sadbhaw Scholarship in any way possible. Let''s take a common goal of providing equal educational opportunities to those in need and making a difference.', 'Yangkee Ghale', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'asdasdasdasd', '', '', '2016-09-03 16:05:27', '2016-09-03 16:05:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sadbhaw/?post_type=leader&#038;p=1867', 0, 'leader', '', 0),
(1868, 1, '2016-08-13 09:54:06', '2016-08-13 09:54:06', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sarala Thapa is the UK lead for Sadbhaw Schoalrships. Sarala believes making a difference starts with an individual''s willingness to help.  As a UK chapter she hopes to raise awareness and extend this cause to gather help from more  probable contributors for many more kids in Nepal.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Visiting different parts of Nepal and meeting people from different walks of life has been very eye opening for her. She believes education is the most important tool to help a child meet their full potential.  Unfortunately, many young children are unable to attend school in Nepal. Sarala has a firm believe of making a difference starts with an individual''s willingness to help. After learning about Sadbhaw from a good friend, she also wanted make my small contribution. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sarala is currently sponsoring Nani Maya Lho from Makwanpur. It gives her immense happiness to know little contribution is helping a child receive the education she deserves. She hopes to commit to sponsor more children in the future.</span>', 'Sarala Thapa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'asdasdasd-adas', '', '', '2016-11-08 05:22:49', '2016-11-08 05:22:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sadbhaw/?post_type=leader&#038;p=1868', 0, 'leader', '', 0),
